1. FEATURES
-----------

- Package creation – Build `.rawdist` archives from a directory
  containing a `rawdist.conf`.
- Checksum integrity – Automatic SHA256 generation and verification
  of every file in the package.
- Download & cache – Fetch packages from URLs with a pluggable
  HTTP client (trait based), storing them in a local cache.
- Install & remove – Full install/uninstall workflow with
  configurable target directories (template placeholders).
- Manifest tracking – Record installed packages in a TOML file.
- Lock file support – Pin exact package versions, sources, and
  checksums for reproducible environments.
- File filtering – Glob‑based include/exclude patterns.
- High‑level API – `PackageManager` struct provides a unified
  interface for all operations.
- Abstract file system – The `FileSystem` trait allows mocking for
  unit tests and custom storage backends.
- Pluggable HTTP – The `HttpClient` trait lets you swap the
  download implementation (e.g., for offline testing).
- Rich error handling – All errors implement `miette::Diagnostic`
  with codes and help texts.
- Security – Path traversal prevention, file type whitelisting,
  and archive size limits during extraction.
- Edition support – Each config specifies an `edition`, ensuring
  forward compatibility.


2. INSTALLATION
---------------

2.1 Add to Cargo.toml
    Since the crate is not published on crates.io yet, add it as a git
    dependency:

        [dependencies]
        librawdist = { git = "https://github.com/mroczect/librawdist.git" }

    Or specify a tag:

        librawdist = { git = "https://github.com/mroczect/librawdist.git", tag = "v0.5.0" }

2.2 Build from source
    Requirements: Rust (edition 2021+), Git.

        git clone https://github.com/mroczect/librawdist.git
        cd librawdist
        cargo build --release

    The library will be compiled and can be used by other projects via
    path dependency:

        [dependencies]
        librawdist = { path = "../librawdist" }


3. QUICK START
--------------

    use librawdist::{
        create_package,
        RawdistConfig,
        fs::RealFs,
    };

    fn main() -> Result<(), Box<dyn std::error::Error>> {
        let fs = RealFs;
        let config = RawdistConfig::load_from_dir(&fs, "my_theme".as_ref())?;
        create_package(
            &fs,
            "my_theme".as_ref(),
            "my_theme.rawdist".as_ref(),
            &config,
        )?;
        println!("Package created.");
        Ok(())
    }

    For more detailed usage, see sections 4.6, 4.7, and 9.


4. LIBRARY USAGE (RUST API)
----------------------------

4.1 Modules overview
    The library exposes these public modules:

        librawdist::checksum   – SHA256 hashing, formatting, and parsing
        librawdist::error      – error types (RawdistError)
        librawdist::fetch      – download .rawdist files via HTTP
        librawdist::filter     – glob include/exclude logic
        librawdist::fs         – FileSystem trait and RealFs implementation
        librawdist::install    – install and remove packages
        librawdist::lock       – lock file structures and operations
        librawdist::manager    – high‑level PackageManager facade
        librawdist::manifest   – manifest load/save
        librawdist::package    – create, extract, and move packages
        librawdist::types      – configuration and manifest data types
        librawdist::verify     – verify a package's integrity

    Re‑exported items (convenience):

        - librawdist::RawdistError
        - librawdist::RawdistConfig
        - librawdist::Manifest
        - librawdist::LockFile
        - librawdist::FileSystem
        - librawdist::RealFs
        - librawdist::HttpClient
        - librawdist::UreqClient
        - librawdist::PackageManager
        - librawdist::fetch_package
        - librawdist::install_package
        - librawdist::remove_package
        - librawdist::create_package
        - librawdist::extract_to_temp
        - librawdist::move_extracted
        - librawdist::verify_package
        - librawdist::load_manifest
        - librawdist::save_manifest

4.2 Key types

    4.2.1 RawdistConfig
        The top‑level configuration deserialized from `rawdist.conf`.
        Fields:
            edition   : String (default "1") – config format version
            package   : PackageMeta
            rawssg    : RawssgReqs
            files     : FilePatterns
            install   : InstallConfig
            metadata  : toml::value::Table (arbitrary extra data)

        Methods:
            validate() -> Result<(), RawdistError>
                Checks package name, version, target_dir safety,
                include patterns, merge_config, and edition.
            load_from_dir(fs: &dyn FileSystem, dir: &Path) -> Result<Self>
                Reads `rawdist.conf` from a directory and validates it.
            resolve_target_dir() -> String
                Replaces `{{ package.name }}` and `{{ package.version }}`
                placeholders in the configured target_dir.
            new(package, rawssg, files, install) -> Self
                Constructor with default edition and empty metadata.

    4.2.2 PackageMeta
        Metadata describing the package.
        Fields:
            name            : String
            version         : String (semver)
            description     : Option<String>
            authors         : Option<Vec<String>>
            license         : Option<String>
            repository      : Option<String>
            homepage        : Option<String>
            documentation   : Option<String>
            keywords        : Option<Vec<String>>
            categories      : Option<Vec<String>>
            release_date    : Option<String>

    4.2.3 RawssgReqs
        Requirements for the Rawssg runtime.
        Fields:
            min_version   : Option<String>
            max_version   : Option<String>
            r#type        : String (must be present, no default)

    4.2.4 FilePatterns
        Inclusion and exclusion patterns (glob syntax).
        Fields:
            include   : Vec<String>  (required, no default)
            exclude   : Vec<String>  (optional, defaults to empty)

    4.2.5 InstallConfig
        Installation parameters.
        Fields:
            target_dir    : String   (required)
            merge_config  : Option<String> (optional, relative path)

    4.2.6 InstalledPackage
        Record of an installed package.
        Fields:
            name            : String
            version         : String
            install_path    : PathBuf (absolute)
            config_merged   : Option<String>

    4.2.7 Manifest
        TOML‑serialisable manifest tracking installed packages.
        Fields:
            packages : Vec<InstalledPackage>

        Implements Default (empty manifest).

    4.2.8 LockFile / LockEntry
        Lock file for reproducible installations.
        LockEntry fields: name, version, source, checksum.
        LockFile { packages: Vec<LockEntry> }
        Methods:
            load(fs: &dyn FileSystem, path: &Path) -> Result<LockFile>
            save(fs: &dyn FileSystem, path: &Path) -> Result<()>
            add_package(&mut self, name, version, source, checksum)

    4.2.9 RawdistError
        Comprehensive error enum with `thiserror` and `miette` derive.
        Variants:
            Io(std::io::Error)
            Config(String)
            TomlParse { path, source }
            ChecksumMismatch { path }
            MissingFile { path }
            Manifest(String)
            NotInstalled(String)
            WalkDir(walkdir::Error)
            InvalidInput(String)
            Validation(String)
            VersionMismatch { name, required, current }
            PathTraversal(PathBuf)
            Network(String)
            ArchiveTooLarge { size, max }

        Each variant includes a diagnostic code and, where appropriate,
        a help message.

    4.2.10 FileSystem (trait)
        Trait abstracting filesystem operations for testability.
        Methods:
            read_to_string, read, write, create_dir_all, remove_dir_all,
            remove_file, exists, is_dir, is_file, read_dir, copy_file,
            rename, canonicalize, walk_dir, metadata.

        The standard implementation is `RealFs`, which delegates to
        `std::fs`. Users can provide mock implementations for testing.

    4.2.11 HttpClient (trait)
        Trait for fetching raw bytes from a URL.
        Method:
            get(&self, url: &str) -> Result<Vec<u8>, RawdistError>

        Built‑in implementation: `UreqClient` (using the `ureq` crate).

    4.2.12 PackageManager
        High‑level facade that combines filesystem, HTTP, manifest, and
        lock file handling.

        Constructor:
            PackageManager::new(fs, http, manifest_path, lockfile_path)

        Methods:
            install(&self, archive_path, target_override) -> Result<()>
                Installs a local .rawdist file and updates the lock file.
            install_from_url(&self, url, target_override) -> Result<()>
                Downloads and then installs.
            uninstall(&self, package_name) -> Result<()>
                Removes the package and syncs the lock file.
            verify(&self, archive_path, keep_temp) -> Result<Option<PathBuf>>
                Verifies a package; if `keep_temp` is true, returns the
                extracted directory path.
            list(&self) -> Result<Manifest>
                Returns the current manifest.
            create(&self, src_dir, output_path, config) -> Result<()>
                Creates a new .rawdist package.

4.3 Public functions

    All functions below require a `&dyn FileSystem` (and some also
    `&dyn HttpClient`) as their first argument(s).

    4.3.1 fetch_package(fs, client, url, dest_path) -> Result<PathBuf>
        Downloads a `.rawdist` file from a URL. If `dest_path` is None,
        saves to `$CACHE_DIR/librawdist/cache/` using the filename from
        the URL. Returns the path to the downloaded file.

    4.3.2 create_package(fs, src_dir, output_path, config) -> Result<()>
        Creates a `.rawdist` archive from a source directory.
        Steps:
            1. Generate checksums of all matching files.
            2. Append those files into a tar.gz archive.
            3. Add `checksums.sha256` to the archive.
            4. Compress and write to `output_path`.

    4.3.3 extract_to_temp(fs, archive_path) -> Result<PathBuf>
        Extracts a `.rawdist` archive into a temporary directory,
        verifies every file against the embedded `checksums.sha256`,
        and returns the path to the extracted directory (kept alive).
        Aborts if the archive exceeds 500 MB, contains path traversal,
        non‑regular file types, or checksum mismatches.

    4.3.4 move_extracted(fs, src, target) -> Result<()>
        Renames the extracted directory to the final target directory.
        Fails if target already exists.

    4.3.5 install_package(fs, archive_path, target_override, manifest_path) -> Result<()>
        Full installation routine:
            1. Validate the file is a `.rawdist`.
            2. Extract and verify.
            3. Load `rawdist.conf` from the extracted directory.
            4. Resolve target directory (override or config template).
            5. Reject if target already exists.
            6. Move extracted content to target.
            7. Update the manifest file.

    4.3.6 remove_package(fs, package_name, manifest_path) -> Result<()>
        Removes an installed package by deleting its directory and
        updating the manifest.

    4.3.7 verify_package(fs, archive_path, keep_temp) -> Result<Option<PathBuf>>
        Verifies a `.rawdist` archive by extracting to temp and checking
        all checksums. If `keep_temp` is true, the extracted directory
        is returned (caller must clean up). Otherwise it is deleted and
        `None` is returned.

4.4 Checksum utilities
    Functions in `librawdist::checksum`:

        hash_file(fs, path) -> Result<String>
        generate_checksums(fs, root, patterns) -> Result<BTreeMap<PathBuf, String>>
        format_checksums(&BTreeMap) -> String
        parse_checksums(content) -> Result<BTreeMap<PathBuf, String>>

4.5 Filter utilities
    `librawdist::filter::is_included(rel_path, includes, excludes) -> bool`
    Returns true if the relative path matches any include pattern and
    is not excluded. Exclude takes priority.

4.6 Integration example (low‑level API)

    use librawdist::{
        fs::RealFs,
        fetch::UreqClient,
        fetch_package,
        install_package,
        remove_package,
        verify_package,
        RawdistError,
    };
    use std::path::Path;

    fn main() -> Result<(), RawdistError> {
        let fs = RealFs;
        let client = UreqClient;
        let manifest = Path::new("rawdist-manifest.toml");

        // Download
        let archive = fetch_package(
            &fs,
            &client,
            "https://example.org/my-theme.rawdist",
            None,
        )?;

        // Verify (optional, install also verifies)
        verify_package(&fs, &archive, false)?;

        // Install
        install_package(&fs, &archive, None, manifest)?;

        // Later, remove
        remove_package(&fs, "my-theme", manifest)?;

        Ok(())
    }

4.7 Integration example (high‑level with PackageManager)

    use librawdist::{
        fs::RealFs,
        fetch::UreqClient,
        PackageManager,
        RawdistError,
    };
    use std::path::PathBuf;

    fn main() -> Result<(), RawdistError> {
        let fs = RealFs;
        let client = UreqClient;
        let mgr = PackageManager::new(
            &fs,
            &client,
            PathBuf::from("rawdist-manifest.toml"),
            PathBuf::from("rawdist.lock"),
        );

        // Install from URL
        mgr.install_from_url("https://example.org/my-theme.rawdist", None)?;

        // List installed packages
        let manifest = mgr.list()?;
        println!("{:#?}", manifest);

        // Uninstall
        mgr.uninstall("my-theme")?;

        Ok(())
    }


5. CONFIGURATION (rawdist.conf)
-------------------------------

5.1 Format
    A file named `rawdist.conf` placed in the root of the package source.
    It must be valid TOML. The `edition` field is recommended; if omitted
    it defaults to `"1"`.

    Example:

        edition = "1"

        [package]
        name = "my-theme"
        version = "1.0.0"
        description = "A beautiful theme"
        authors = ["Author <email@example.com>"]
        license = "MIT"
        repository = "https://github.com/user/repo"

        [rawssg]
        min_version = "0.5.0"
        type = "theme"

        [files]
        include = ["layouts/**/*", "assets/**/*", "rawdist.conf"]
        exclude = ["*.log", "tmp/**"]

        [install]
        target_dir = "themes/{{ package.name }}"
        merge_config = "user.conf"

        [metadata]
        custom_key = "value"

5.2 Fields detail
    - edition              : Config format version. Currently only "1" is valid.
    - package.name         : alphanumeric, '-' or '_' only.
    - package.version      : valid semver (e.g. "1.2.3").
    - rawssg.min_version   : optional minimum Rawssg version.
    - rawssg.max_version   : optional maximum compatible version.
    - rawssg.type          : package type (e.g. "theme", "plugin").
    - files.include        : list of glob patterns to include (mandatory).
    - files.exclude        : list of glob patterns to exclude.
    - install.target_dir   : relative path; may contain `{{ package.name }}`
                             and `{{ package.version }}` placeholders.
    - install.merge_config : optional file to merge into existing configs.
    - metadata             : free‑form TOML table.

5.3 Validation rules
    `RawdistConfig::validate()` enforces:
        - package name is not empty and only contains allowed characters.
        - version parses as a valid semver.
        - target_dir is relative and does not contain `..`.
        - files.include is not empty.
        - merge_config (if present) is relative and safe.
        - edition exactly matches `CURRENT_EDITION` ("1").


6. PACKAGE FORMAT (.rawdist)
----------------------------

6.1 Internal structure
    A `.rawdist` file is a gzip‑compressed tar archive containing:
        - All files matching the include/exclude patterns,
          preserving their relative paths.
        - A file named `checksums.sha256` at the root of the archive.

6.2 checksums.sha256 format
    One entry per line, hash and relative path separated by two spaces.
    Example:

        e3b0c44298fc1c149afbf4c8996fb92427ae41e4649b934ca495991b7852b855  rawdist.conf
        8f2e5...  layouts/default.html

6.3 Security: path traversal & file type filtering
    During extraction, every entry path is checked for `..` components
    and the canonical destination is verified to stay within the
    extraction root. Only regular files and directories are allowed;
    symlinks, hardlinks, and device nodes are rejected. The maximum
    archive size is 500 MB (checked before reading).


7. MANIFEST AND LOCK FILES
--------------------------

7.1 Manifest (installed packages)
    A TOML file (typically `rawdist-manifest.toml`) tracking currently
    installed packages. Maintained by `install_package` and `remove_package`.

    Structure:
        [[packages]]
        name = "my-theme"
        version = "1.0.0"
        install_path = "/absolute/path/to/themes/my-theme"
        config_merged = "user.conf"

    The manifest is loaded with `load_manifest(fs, path)` and saved with
    `save_manifest(fs, path, &manifest)`.

7.2 Lock file (pinned versions)
    A TOML file (e.g., `rawdist.lock`) for reproducible environments.
    Each entry records: name, version, source URL, and checksum (SHA256
    of the `.rawdist` file).

    Structure:
        [[packages]]
        name = "my-theme"
        version = "1.0.0"
        source = "https://.../my-theme.rawdist"
        checksum = "abc123..."

    Loaded/saved via `LockFile::load` and `save`. The `PackageManager`
    automatically synchronises the lock file with the manifest after
    install/uninstall.


8. ERROR HANDLING
-----------------

All fallible functions return `Result<T, RawdistError>`. The error enum
provides rich diagnostics when used with `miette` (e.g., in a CLI):

    Error: Checksum verification failed for file layouts/broken.html
      Diagnostic code: librawdist::checksum_mismatch
      Help: The package may be corrupted or tampered. Download again from official source.

When using the library programmatically, you can match on the variants:

    match err {
        RawdistError::ChecksumMismatch { path } => { ... },
        RawdistError::MissingFile { path } => { ... },
        ...
    }


9. EXAMPLES
-----------

9.1 Building a package

    use librawdist::fs::RealFs;
    use librawdist::types::RawdistConfig;
    use librawdist::create_package;

    fn main() -> Result<(), librawdist::RawdistError> {
        let fs = RealFs;
        let src = std::path::Path::new("my_theme");
        let config = RawdistConfig::load_from_dir(&fs, src)?;
        create_package(&fs, src, std::path::Path::new("my_theme.rawdist"), &config)?;
        Ok(())
    }

9.2 Installing a package

    use librawdist::fs::RealFs;
    use librawdist::fetch::UreqClient;
    use librawdist::{fetch_package, install_package};

    fn main() -> Result<(), librawdist::RawdistError> {
        let fs = RealFs;
        let client = UreqClient;
        let archive = fetch_package(
            &fs,
            &client,
            "https://example.org/packages/my_theme.rawdist",
            None,
        )?;
        install_package(
            &fs,
            &archive,
            None,
            std::path::Path::new("rawdist-manifest.toml"),
        )?;
        Ok(())
    }

9.3 Removing a package

    use librawdist::fs::RealFs;
    use librawdist::remove_package;

    fn main() -> Result<(), librawdist::RawdistError> {
        let fs = RealFs;
        remove_package(
            &fs,
            "my_theme",
            std::path::Path::new("rawdist-manifest.toml"),
        )?;
        Ok(())
    }

9.4 Verifying a package

    use librawdist::fs::RealFs;
    use librawdist::verify_package;

    fn main() -> Result<(), librawdist::RawdistError> {
        let fs = RealFs;
        // Keep the extracted directory for inspection
        let extracted = verify_package(
            &fs,
            std::path::Path::new("downloaded.rawdist"),
            true,
        )?;
        if let Some(dir) = extracted {
            println!("Package verified and extracted to {}", dir.display());
            // clean up manually
            std::fs::remove_dir_all(&dir)?;
        }
        Ok(())
    }

9.5 Using the PackageManager

    use librawdist::fs::RealFs;
    use librawdist::fetch::UreqClient;
    use librawdist::PackageManager;
    use std::path::PathBuf;

    fn main() -> Result<(), librawdist::RawdistError> {
        let fs = RealFs;
        let client = UreqClient;
        let mgr = PackageManager::new(
            &fs,
            &client,
            PathBuf::from("rawdist-manifest.toml"),
            PathBuf::from("rawdist.lock"),
        );

        // Download and install
        mgr.install_from_url(
            "https://example.org/packages/my_theme.rawdist",
            None,
        )?;

        // Create a new package from a local directory
        let config = librawdist::RawdistConfig::load_from_dir(
            &fs,
            "another_theme".as_ref(),
        )?;
        mgr.create(
            "another_theme".as_ref(),
            "another_theme.rawdist".as_ref(),
            &config,
        )?;

        Ok(())
    }


10. CONTRIBUTING
----------------

Contributions are welcome! Please open issues or pull requests on the
GitHub repository. Before submitting:
    - Ensure the code compiles without warnings.
    - Existing tests pass (`cargo test`).
    - New functionality should include unit tests (using mock filesystem
      and HTTP implementations) and documentation updates.

Contact the maintainer via the repository's issue tracker.


